.TH "allocate_resource" 9 "allocate_resource" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
allocate_resource \- allocate empty slot in the resource tree given range & alignment. The resource will be reallocated with a new size if it was already allocated
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" allocate_resource
.BI "(struct resource *root "  ","
.BI "struct resource *new "  ","
.BI "resource_size_t size "  ","
.BI "resource_size_t min "  ","
.BI "resource_size_t max "  ","
.BI "resource_size_t align "  ","
.BI "resource_size_t (*alignf)(void *, const struct resource *, resource_size_t, resource_size_t) "  ","
.BI "void *alignf_data "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "root" 12
root resource descriptor
.IP "new" 12
resource descriptor desired by caller
.IP "size" 12
requested resource region size
.IP "min" 12
minimum boundary to allocate
.IP "max" 12
maximum boundary to allocate
.IP "align" 12
alignment requested, in bytes
.IP "alignf" 12
alignment function, optional, called if not NULL
.IP "alignf_data" 12
arbitrary data to pass to the \fIalignf\fP function
